import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of opening prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Opening Prices")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['close'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Closing Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of closing prices over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.grid(True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['high'], data['low'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('High')
    ax.set_ylabel('Low')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the highest and lowest prices of the stock?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title('What is the distribution of trading volumes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
